- Distribution Channels: {{ brief_result.distribution_channels | join(', ') if brief_result.distribution_channels else 'Not specified' }}

───────────────────────────────────────
KEYWORD PLACEMENT REQUIREMENTS
───────────────────────────────────────

Main Keyword "{{ all_keywords.main_keyword }}":
- Title: must appear, preferably in first 3 words
- Introduction: must appear within first 100 words
- Headings: must appear in at least 2 H2 headings
- Conclusion: must appear in final paragraph
- Target density: 1–2%

Primary keywords: use in H2/H3 headings and first 3 paragraphs (density: 0.5–1% each)
Secondary keywords: use as supporting variations throughout body (density: 0.3–0.5% each)
LSI keywords: use for semantic depth; no specific density target
Long-tail keywords: use in FAQ sections and question-based content
{% if seo_result.keyword_clusters %}
Organize content around keyword clusters for thematic depth.
{% endif %}

───────────────────────────────────────
HEADER REQUIREMENTS
───────────────────────────────────────

ALL headers must be content-specific and keyword-rich — NEVER generic placeholders.

NEVER USE: Introduction, Conclusion, Summary, Overview, Final Thoughts, Getting Started
GOOD EXAMPLES:
- "Implementing {{ all_keywords.main_keyword }} for Marketing Success"
- "Key Takeaways for Your {{ all_keywords.main_keyword }} Strategy"

───────────────────────────────────────
ARTICLE DELIVERABLES
───────────────────────────────────────

- article_title: 50–60 chars, includes main_keyword (preferably first 3 words)
- article_content: full article in markdown (not a summary)
- outline: list of H2-level headers (content-specific, keyword-rich — NOT generic)
- hook: 50–100 words opening hook; include main_keyword naturally
- key_takeaways: 3–5 strings reinforcing main messages from marketing brief
- call_to_action: 20–50 words aligned with marketing brief KPIs

